##

EXAMPLE: tests/number_separators.stult

This test checks apostrophe separators in number literals.

Apostrophes may be written between digits to make large numbers easier to
read. They do not change the numeric value.

##

ASSERT : STD.ERROR.ASSERT
NUMBER : STD.TYPE.NUMBER

ASSERT.EQUAL(1'000, 1000, "apostrophes should be accepted in whole-number literals")
ASSERT.EQUAL(1'000'000'000, 1000000000, "multiple apostrophe groups should be accepted")
ASSERT.EQUAL(123'456.789'123, 123456.789123, "apostrophes should be accepted around decimal digits")
ASSERT.EQUAL(.123'456, 0.123456, "apostrophes should be accepted in dot-prefixed decimal literals")
ASSERT.EQUAL(1'000%, 10, "apostrophe separators should work before percentage suffixes")
ASSERT.EQUAL(1e1'0, 10000000000, "apostrophe separators should work in exponent digits")
ASSERT.EQUAL(NUMBER.NEW("59'872"), 59872, "NUMBER.NEW should parse apostrophe-separated number strings")
ASSERT.EQUAL(NUMBER.FORMAT(1'000'000, 0, {.GROUP_DIGITS: +}), "1'000'000", "FORMAT should accept separated number literals")
